The paper focuses on decentralized control of mobile robots for coverage problems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of local coordination rules and clustering techniques suggests a focus on multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The investigation of cyclic behavior and the development of a similarity measure for achieving consensus suggest a focus on control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of computer simulations and potential applications in sensing coverage suggest a focus on computer vision (cs.CV).
